						               													<description>Match Ball is a simulation game of a Tennis match competition. You can emulate your favorite tennis players with this game. I designed the game as a simulation where you can reproduce all the movements and strikes a professional player can do in a match!  You can play as a single player match or doubles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You have one counter representing you in the court and must move around the field to send the ball to the other side while re-positioning yourself in the best way that you can to cover your side and catch the returning strike from the other player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You have all the possible strikes in a tennis match that can be done: Serves, Forehand, Backhand, passing shots, lobs, smashes, etc...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The components are:&amp;#10;- Tennis court (Grass)&amp;#10;- Rulebook&amp;#10;- Strike Rule (To be printed in transparency)&amp;#10;- Balls and players counters&amp;#10;- Markers&amp;#10;- Action cards&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You will need to provide with 4 dice: 2 color d6, 1 white d6 and a 1d4.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is my first attempt to design a game. I came up with the idea when creating the geeklist 1:1 scale Sports boardgames that lists games of sports.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
